annotation.TEXT: I don't think I've ever seen an SMW hack lag like that before!
Whoa, they're of the bounce-on-all-sides variety!

Unfortunately, not hitting the goal tape at all really hurts my average, but I just had to go for that huge combo there! (However, I transformed 7 enemies into coins, so I would've gotten 4 lives and some change anyway...)
I'm guessing that one-way rope is there to prevent me from accessing that mushroom from the wrong side. (But I'd still have to stand on the moving platform over the lava to reach it anyway...)
Oh, man. Football Chuck. This could get dangerous really quickly.
Nope. It's boss time, against Morton! Well, this'll be a piece of cake.
What, a boss door already? But I only have two ! coins... Oh, but what's up here?
Wow, I think I'm lucky that the turn block bridge didn't crush me against the wall there. (I know that they can do that.)
Ah, that's better!
No Yoshis because they're all at a casino playing BJ right now.
There's some more high coins, which I guess I could bounce off of footballs to reach...
Wait, this level looks familiar... I think this is the title demo level, but with enemies in it!

16-hit combo! Nope, nothing. (Too bad this isn't that one part in Sonic the Hedgehog where you could break 17 blocks in a row, and if you did so without screwing up the combo, the last 2 blocks would be worth 10,000 points each!)
Goal tape average so far: 64 / 2 = 32 stars each.
I think the terrain is slightly modified as well, but I'm pretty sure this is indeed based off of the title demo level (or vice versa).
Ow, the extreme corner of my hitbox again! Fortunately, there's a bunch of yellow ! blocks around here, so I can replace my lost mushrooms several times!
MEGA KILL!
...What the? Are the four bullet shooter sprites on the same spot there? Whoops, I think BBKaizo screwed up with their positions...
Whoa, I nearly ran right into that koopa. That would've sucked, since I just absent-mindedly grabbed that mushroom that I meant to save for later.
Ow, my groin!
Whoa, nearly got bones jammed up my feet there.
BGM: Sonic the Hedgehog (Genesis) - Green Hill Zone

Well, for the most part, the main OW looks unedited. Alright, Berry Plains most likely has 2 exits, so you guys get to vote now! Place your votes for whether you want me to go the normal way or the secret way after I'm done with Berry Plains! To be continued... Yo!
Goal tape average so far: 64 / 3 = 21.333 stars each.

Now, I wonder if the title demo's inputs were recorded using this version of the level, and that's why BJ on the title screen seemed to make a lot of unusual actions... Perhaps he was meant to be fighting enemies and riding HB platforms and such.
Heck, yeah. Killing a football with my head just because my butt's on the ground!
Whoa, lucky stomp there. I'm glad his pointy bones weren't sticking straight up at that moment.
Oh, man. I've wasted too much time fooling around...
That unlocks First Castle, and BJ2 is going to have first dibs on it!
So, is BJ rebelling against Bowser or something? He just defeated one of Bowser's Koopalings, rescued an egg, and is now blowing up this castle!
Wow, I got lucky there! Hmm... Looks like this is an unbreakable turn block (Map16 tile 140).
7-life combo!
Nothing special over here, and it appears that the upper path here is safer, in addition to having the ! coin.
Yeah, I recklessly ran right into that one...
I don't see anything of interest to the left...
Well, that Swooper was kind of pointless. Also, I'm not going to waste time trying to kill every single Spike Top with the vertical edges of the screen.
Oh, man! Cheepos!
Bah, that was horrible! I should've been able to do way better than that!
Umm... Up or down? I'll go down for now.
Whoa, I'm surprised that diagonal Podoboo didn't clip the extreme corner of my hitbox there.
Whoa there, HB!
I obviously want to explore all of the paths here, so that I don't miss any ! coins.
Hey there, Bony Beetle. How's it going?
Why is there a fish out of water here?
Whew, okay! Yes, I ran face-first into that Chuck, but whatever.
Whoa! Quick reaction time FTW!
Oh, man. So many Chucks...
Oh, I definitely remember this 4x4 chunk of turn blocks, but it didn't have Football Charlies on it in the title demo!
Ah, there's the second ! coin.
There were some more high-up coins, though I grabbed most of them by bouncing off of that football. Was I supposed to bounce off of an enemy to reach those other high-up coins I saw before?
4-life combo!
BGM: Yoshi's Safari - Spirit Mountain
Nice, I figured I could slide-kill those upside-down piranha plants. However, I'm not going to try to kill the center one over the munchers, of course.
Hmm... Looks like there's multiple paths...
Alright, BJ2 just unlocked Water Island, which is what BJ1 is going to play right now! (Hmm... This submap seems familiar...)
Aw, I just noticed that there's no special "looking up" animation. Sure, you can still toss things you're carrying upwards, but just simply holding up doesn't cause BJ to look up...
Whoa!!!
...D'oh! I can't just simply jump back up. Maybe I could if I timed a couple jumps properly while sprinting, but I don't want to waste even more time trying, so forget it.
Hello, and welcome back to Bowser Jr.'s Adventure! Alright, I believe it's player 2's turn, and he's going to check out Chuck's Cave!
Ah, a third ! coin. However, I'm still two short. Maybe this boss door doesn't actually lead to the boss yet. Sometimes hackers use that big red door as a regular door...
Uh, huh. I thought the world 1 submap looked familiar. It's the same as the right half of the original Yoshi's Island. And, the main overworld map doesn't look edited at all.
Can't go any further to the right, so does this pipe take me to the "Cave" portion of Chuck's Cave?
Oh, man! More flying cheepos!
Well, hitting that yellow switch in The Village certainly made this part less dangerous!

...Umm, what? "Martin"? ...Okay, so did that Koopaling have his name changed, or was that an impostor Morton, or was he actually a Martian and that's a typo? Also, what's with the empty space between "Martin" and the period after it?
If only I had a fire flower to greatly speed up this fight...
W-H-O-A-!-!-! U-N-U-S-U-A-L L-A-G S-P-I-K-E-!
GAAAMMMEEE!!!
BGM: SMB3 (All-Stars) - Fortress
Oh, this level's got ! coins.
Oh, there's a path to the left here...
Oh, I guess all of the coins around here are purple for whatever reason.
Hello, and welcome back to Bowser Rampages Again! ...Wait, that's not right. That was a different hack, which had Cirno in it. Alright, let me try this again...
There's some frowny clouds and a wall that I don't recall seeing in the title demo...
Nuts, I want to clunk those two shells together.
Aw, just another mushroom. I would kind of like another fire flower... Oh, a Spike Top. They vanish and are considered dead by the game if scrolled off the top or bottom of the screen, like this.
Yet another mushroom. I wonder if that one fire flower back in Sky Mountain was a mistake, and was supposed to have been a mushroom as well...
Nothing special down there, though that would've been a good place to put an ! coin.
I do believe I have just enough time to make an attempt for a decent amount of stars using that Swooper...
Aw, more vanilla cave music?
Geez, I've been fooling around too much again...
You know what? This is risky since I'm low on time, but I want to go back and check out the upper route.
Oh, well. At least I didn't run out of time.
Nope, I doubt it. (Wow, I really expected to get OMNOMNOM-ed there!)
Whoops. Well, that factory's busted, and I don't think I'm getting that shell back now.
Ohhh, I hope the goal is just up ahead!
Oh, good. The cheepos stopped. Now, I wonder if there's anything good in the water between those close-together munchers...
Oh, man. A note block staircase.
BLOCK FACTORYYY!!!
I wonder what I'm missing on the upper route...
Ow, my butt!
Ow, the extreme corner of my hitbox! But, my combo's still going!
Looks like it. Unfortunately, there's no custom music here.
Okay, that was me screwing up and letting the side of the muncher OMNOMNOM me as I was bouncing upward there.
Oh, wait. Maybe it has been edited slightly. There are three ghosts surrounding the Donut Ghost House (possibly called "Berry Ghost House" in this hack).
Whoa, lucky double stomp there. Now, I saw coins way up high, but how do I reach them? Are there hidden blocks around here? Or is the game going to give me a cape soon?
L-L-L-L-LUDICROUS KILL!!!
Alright, now let's see if any of these turn blocks contain anything...
Well, let's move on.
But, it had nothing of interest. However, it's a good path to take to avoid the enemies above.
Huh. Was that purple coin hinting at anything here? ...Doesn't look like it.
(I checked that upper route later, and there appears to be just enemies and coins up there. Nothing special.)
Alright, whatever. I'll let that last Chuck live. Now I believe over here is the dead end where the title demo ended.
Oh, man. Water.
I'll leave that mushroom there in case I need it in the near future.
Alright, world 1 of this two-world demo is now complete, and...
